Package net.proteusframework.internet.http.resource Description

Defines a way to describe content by type, size, caching ability and how to retrieve it. Resources are used to provide the content, such as images, from a variety of sources. The Resource interface is the important piece in this class. Implementations of resource can be used to provide images for the user interface, content to be saved to disk by the user, etc.

The URLResource provides content via a URL. As an example, this class can be used with the URL provided by ClassLoader.getResource() to provide content from the class path, such as from a JAR file.

The JDBCResourceManager provides an efficient way to provide content from a JDBC connection.
